Firstly let’s find out the price per unit fruit type based on their relationships to others. We know Watermelon Cost (WC) equals Pepper Price ($P$) multiplied by 3. And Orange Cost (OC) equals WC minus 5 $. Thus we can express these relationships as follows;
$WC=3*P$
$OC=(WC)-5$. As it was provided that P=$15$, plugging this into our first equation yields;
$WC=3*$15=\$45$. Substituting this value back into second equation leads us to $\ OC=($45$-5)=\$40$. 
Knowing all prices individually allows you determine individual quantities using information about units purchased.
